data.description: This home is nestled on the outskirts of the City of Clayton on 4.3 agriculturally zoned acres.  Has been a multi generational property used for gardening, horticulture, and homesteading.  There are parts of the acreage that has never been developed and could be subdivided for other uses if correct rezoning was applied for and obtained from the county. It has great multiple access points to US 441. The home sits  quaintly on a hillside with breath taking views of Tiger, and Glassy mountains, and the front porch is your front seat to some breathtaking sunsets to the west. Phenomenal wrap around drive. Home needs some finishing touches, the owner will look at all reasonable offers, and will be open to negotiating. Perfect 3 bedroom, 1 1/2 bath, with partial finished basement with another bathroom stubbed in on this level. Basement has interior and exterior access and two partially finished rooms on this level also.  Yards boast well developed gorgeous landscapes! Master on main! Oversized living, dining, and has a great country kitchen.  Stoned hearth fireplace, new laminate in living, dining, and kitchen area.  Main bath recently renovated.  Parts of the home still need updating, current owner has given the home a great start on updating. There are several outdoor storage sheds and barns about the property used for gardening, livestock, and storage. Owner had previously planned for a mobile home on the flat area adjacent to the house, there is a separate septic system installed there currently for a 3 bedroom system should new owner want to subdivide to build or put in a mobile home there. The potential for this property is great for future expansion, or you can keep the whole 4.3 acres and utilize how you'd like.
